{"title":"2024 Center for Metal Arts Bicycle Framebuilding Course 10/21 – 11/1","link":"https://theradavist.com/2024-center-for-metal-arts-bicycle-framebuilding-course/","date":1724685199000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1620\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Bike_Building_Course.jpg?fit=1200,1080&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Bike_Building_Course.jpg?w=1620&amp;quality=75 1620w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Bike_Building_Course.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Bike_Building_Course.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Bike_Building_Course.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Our friends at the <a href=\"https://centerformetalarts.org/product/steel-brazed-frame-building/\" target=\"_blank\">Center for Metal Arts</a> in Johnstown, PA are offering an opportunity to build your own bike frame!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2.png?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/3.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/3.png?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/3.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/3.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/4.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/4.png?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/4.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/4.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p>This two-week workshop will teach you to measure, fit, and braze a Track, Road, Gravel, Cyclocross, or Mountain bike. No prior metalworking experience is necessary!</p>\n<p>Learn more at the <a href=\"https://centerformetalarts.org/product/steel-brazed-frame-building/\" target=\"_blank\">Center for Metal Arts</a>!</p>\n<p><em>Photos: <a href=\"http://@jarrodfromhope\" target=\"_blank\">Jarrod Bunk</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2024-center-for-metal-arts-bicycle-framebuilding-course/\">2024 Center for Metal Arts Bicycle Framebuilding Course 10/21 – 11/1</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"Josh Weinberg","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3883a36304a27590f948d5733e1b0a6e2962ca3dbf6a6be9c4167145ab7e8ea2","category":"Cycling"}